DATA LICENSE — STATUS NOTE

The design document (Part 12) proposes Creative Commons Zero (CC0), the
public-domain dedication used by Wikidata, for the DATA contributed to the
Causalontology commons, with attribution surviving as built-in provenance
rather than as a legal obligation.

Until the owner finalizes the data license before public launch, data in
this repository is covered by the repository LICENSE ("The attribution
always; no profit, no problem license." — Apache License 2.0).
